{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1032,"text":"Congratulations."},{"time":2721,"text":"By being here,"},{"time":3945,"text":"listening, alive,"},{"time":5406,"text":"a member of a growing species,"},{"time":7731,"text":"you are one of history's\ngreatest winners --"},{"time":10716,"text":"the culmination of a success story\nfour billion years in the making."},{"time":15768,"text":"You are life's one percent."},{"time":18884,"text":"The losers,"},{"time":20064,"text":"the 99 percent of species\nwho have ever lived,"},{"time":22920,"text":"are dead --"},{"time":24110,"text":"killed by fire, flood, asteroids,"},{"time":27495,"text":"predation, starvation, ice, heat"},{"time":29820,"text":"and the cold math of natural selection."},{"time":33186,"text":"Your ancestors,"},{"time":34410,"text":"back to the earliest fishes,"},{"time":35984,"text":"overcame all these challenges."},{"time":38932,"text":"You are here because\nof golden opportunities"},{"time":41925,"text":"made possible by mass extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45437,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49048,"text":"It's true."},{"time":50223,"text":"The same is true\nof your co-winners and relatives."},{"time":53476,"text":"The 34,000 kinds of fishes."},{"time":56586,"text":"How did we all get so lucky?"},{"time":58710,"text":"Will we continue to win?"},{"time":61278,"text":"I am a fish paleobiologist\nwho uses big data --"},{"time":65257,"text":"the fossil record --"},{"time":66490,"text":"to study how some species win\nand others lose."},{"time":70088,"text":"The living can't tell us;"},{"time":71722,"text":"they know nothing but winning."},{"time":73446,"text":"So, we must speak with the dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75946,"text":"How do we make dead fishes talk?"},{"time":78265,"text":"Museums contain multitudes\nof beautiful fish fossils,"},{"time":82702,"text":"but their real beauty emerges"},{"time":84506,"text":"when combined with the larger\nnumber of ugly, broken fossils,"},{"time":88777,"text":"and reduced to ones and zeros."},{"time":91327,"text":"I can trawl a 500-million-year database\nfor evolutionary patterns."},{"time":96412,"text":"For example,"},{"time":97590,"text":"fish forms can be captured by coordinates"},{"time":101361,"text":"and transformed to reveal\nmajor pathways of change"},{"time":105491,"text":"and trends through time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108583,"text":"Here is the story\nof the winners and losers"},{"time":110944,"text":"of just one pivotal event\nI discovered using fossil data."},{"time":115500,"text":"Let's travel back 360 million years --"},{"time":119996,"text":"six times as long ago\nas the last dinosaur --"},{"time":123560,"text":"to the Devonian period;"},{"time":125230,"text":"a strange world."},{"time":127505,"text":"Armored predators\nwith razor-edge jaws dominated"},{"time":131390,"text":"alongside huge fishes\nwith arm bones in their fins."},{"time":137106,"text":"Crab-like fishes scuttled\nacross the sea floor."},{"time":141278,"text":"The few ray-fin relatives\nof salmon and tuna"},{"time":144785,"text":"cowered at the bottom of the food chain."},{"time":148217,"text":"The few early sharks\nlived offshore in fear."},{"time":152900,"text":"Your few four-legged ancestors,\nthe tetrapods,"},{"time":156676,"text":"struggled in tropical river plains."},{"time":160391,"text":"Ecosystems were crowded."},{"time":162744,"text":"There was no escape,"},{"time":164623,"text":"no opportunity in sight."},{"time":167110,"text":"Then the world ended."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168888,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170862,"text":"No, it is a good thing."},{"time":172251,"text":"96 percent of all fish species died"},{"time":176643,"text":"during the Hangenberg event,\n359 million years ago:"},{"time":181127,"text":"an interval of fire and ice."},{"time":183516,"text":"A crowded world was disrupted\nand swept away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187735,"text":"Now, you might think\nthat's the end of the story."},{"time":190260,"text":"The mighty fell,\nthe meek inherited the earth,"},{"time":192475,"text":"and here we are."},{"time":194660,"text":"But winning is not that simple."},{"time":198168,"text":"The handful of survivors\ncame from many groups --"},{"time":201357,"text":"all greatly outnumbered by their own dead."},{"time":204327,"text":"They ranged from top predator\nto bottom-feeder,"},{"time":207084,"text":"big to small,"},{"time":208408,"text":"marine to freshwater."},{"time":210405,"text":"The extinction was a filter."},{"time":212421,"text":"It merely leveled the playing field."},{"time":215352,"text":"What really counted was what survivors did\nover the next several million years"},{"time":220794,"text":"in that devastated world."},{"time":224033,"text":"The former overlords\nshould have had an advantage."},{"time":227245,"text":"They became even larger,"},{"time":229109,"text":"storing energy,"},{"time":230527,"text":"investing in their young,"},{"time":232174,"text":"spreading across the globe,"},{"time":233860,"text":"feasting on fishes,"},{"time":235353,"text":"keeping what had always worked,\nand biding their time."},{"time":238906,"text":"Yet they merely persisted for a while,"},{"time":241947,"text":"declining without innovating,"},{"time":244018,"text":"becoming living fossils."},{"time":246887,"text":"They were too stuck in their ways"},{"time":248872,"text":"and are now largely forgotten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252366,"text":"A few of the long-suffering ray-fins,\nsharks and four-legged tetrapods"},{"time":257549,"text":"went the opposite direction."},{"time":259528,"text":"They became smaller --"},{"time":261264,"text":"living fast,\ndying young,"},{"time":263108,"text":"eating little\nand reproducing rapidly."},{"time":265687,"text":"They tried new foods,"},{"time":267678,"text":"different homes,"},{"time":268907,"text":"strange heads\nand weird bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271282,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272488,"text":"And they found opportunity, proliferated,"},{"time":275472,"text":"and won the future\nfor their 60,000 living species,"},{"time":279451,"text":"including you."},{"time":280846,"text":"That's why they look familiar."},{"time":282489,"text":"You know their names."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285635,"text":"Winning is not about random events"},{"time":288136,"text":"or an arms race."},{"time":289619,"text":"Rather, survivors went down alternative,\nevolutionary pathways."},{"time":294294,"text":"Some found incredible success,"},{"time":296843,"text":"while others became dead fish walking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300572,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302909,"text":"A real scientific term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304540,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306747,"text":"I am now investigating"},{"time":307939,"text":"how these pathways to victory and defeat\nrepeat across time."},{"time":312075,"text":"My lab has already compiled thousands\nupon thousands of dead fishes,"},{"time":316221,"text":"but many more remain."},{"time":317893,"text":"However, it is already clear"},{"time":319774,"text":"that your ancestors' survival\nthrough mass extinction,"},{"time":323478,"text":"and their responses in the aftermath"},{"time":325946,"text":"made you who you are today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328262,"text":"What does this tell us for the future?"},{"time":330405,"text":"As long as a handful of species survive,"},{"time":333183,"text":"life will recover."},{"time":335281,"text":"The versatile and the lucky\nwill not just replace what was lost,"},{"time":339178,"text":"but win in new forms."},{"time":341121,"text":"It just might take several million years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344639,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345813,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}